      • CKR_CANCEL

        public static final int CKR_CANCEL
        When a function executing in serial with an application decides to give the application a chance to do some work, it calls an application-supplied function with a CKN_SURRENDER callback . If the callback returns the value CKR_CANCEL, then the function aborts and returns CKR_FUNCTION_CANCELED.
